<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-158-528  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 158 528.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computing Canada  Jan 19 1989 v15 n2 p26(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Risky business: good project management is both software andtechnique.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Babin, Ron.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Sound project management in the systems development area requiresboth fundamental management expertise and the ability to utilizesome of the project management tools currently available.andP;  Thesystem development life cycle is the key to understanding thescope of project management.andP;  This cycle can be broken into fourphases, including planning the project, implementation of theplan, monitoring the project to collect data on costs and timeexpended and maintaining overall project control.andP;  A number ofsoftware packages are available to facilitate these phases.andP;  Bothproject management and scheduling software are available, notablySPQR/20 from Software Productivity, Quality and Reliability andEstimacs.andP;  Monitoring software is invaluable for collecting costsand progress data.andP;  Another valuable project software is thatwhich is bundled with a proprietary system.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Project Management SystemsCustom SoftwareManagement by ObjectivesPlanningImplementationDecision Support Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>